    • Method Detail

      • parse

        Message parse(JsonNode node,
            ReadableSchemaRegistry registry)
              throws ParsingException
        Parses a JSON node into its corresponding message. Note: schemas only maintain the data relative to the protocol buffer's structure but know nothing of the generated Java type that resulted from the representation's compilation. This method is therefore unable to instantiate messages of the correct subclass. The returned object is however guaranteed to be fully compatible with said generated class and can be safely merged at construction time, e.g.: 
         Schema schema = Schema.of(MyProto.getDescriptorForType())
 Message message = schema.parse(jsonNode);
 MyProto instance = MyProto.newBuilder().mergeFrom(message).build();
        Parameters:
        node - the root node to parse
        Throws:
        ParsingException
